subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Ocellar triangle dark brown, with ca. 2 or 3 setae above ocellar setae. Frons brownish (
Fig. 5M
). Pedicel brownish yellow; first flagellomere yellow (
Fig. 5M
). Clypeus entirely brown. Palpus brownish yellow (
Fig. 5M
). Mesonotum brownish yellow, usually brownish to brown in front of scutellum (
Fig. 5N
). Postpronotal lobe yellow (
Fig. 5O
). Acrostichal setulae in ca. 12–14 irregular rows (
Fig. 5N
). Scutellum brownish yellow to dark brown, black laterally, yellow at tip (
Fig. 5N
). Pleura with a brown to dark brown, longitudinal stripe above (
Fig. 5O
). Katepisternum and mesopleuron mostly yellow (
Fig. 5O
). Wing (
Fig. 2E
): nearly hyaline; costal vein between R 
2+3
and R 
4+5
distally with ca. 4–6 peg-like spinules on ventral surface; R 
4+5
and M 
1
slightly divergent distally; halter mostly yellowish, with a brownish patch at knob (
Fig. 5N
). Abdominal tergites dark brown, 2nd tergite yellow to brownish medially and laterally, 3rd tergite mostly yellow except for lateral region, setigerous laterally and on posterior margin in males (
Fig. 9G
), 3rd tergite yellow anteriorly in females (
Fig. 9H
), 4th tergite yellow anteriorly. Male terminalia: Epandrium lacking pubescence, with ca. 7 setae near posterior and ventral margins per side (
Fig. 21A
). Cercus lacking pubescence (
Fig. 21A
). Surstylus pubescent (
Fig. 21A
). Hypandrium with 1 sensillum (
Fig. 21B
). Paramere narrow basally, pubescent medially, with ca. 5 sensilla distally (
Fig. 21C
).
